WEBVTT

00:00.310 --> 00:01.709
Previously on "God Friended me"...

00:01.710 --> 00:02.719
I appreciate you not mentioning

00:02.719 --> 00:04.059
the whole God Account thing.

00:04.080 --> 00:06.240
Yeah, you know, it was
never my story to tell.

00:06.250 --> 00:07.609
Lester and the board requested

00:07.610 --> 00:09.800
that I come to Harlem
Episcopal to replace you.

00:09.810 --> 00:11.400
I'm being pushed out? Is that it?

00:11.410 --> 00:12.779
Arthur, they're nominating you

00:12.780 --> 00:14.660
to become Bishop of New York.

00:14.670 --> 00:16.920
I've been looking for
someone like you, Rakesh.

00:16.940 --> 00:18.740
Someone who could kind
of be my right hand.

00:18.770 --> 00:21.009
You said it from the beginning, Miles.

00:21.010 --> 00:22.560
You weren't chosen at random.

00:22.570 --> 00:23.799
You just need to find the connection

00:23.800 --> 00:25.960
between you and Simon Hayes.

00:25.980 --> 00:27.960
Come on, you have to
kiss her. It's bad luck.

00:29.000 --> 00:35.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:40.960 --> 00:45.259
So FreeVerse only hosts
11 shows, but 2 of them

00:45.260 --> 00:48.200
made iTunes top 100, so who knows?

00:48.210 --> 00:50.599
Maybe after this meeting
The Millennial Prophet

00:50.600 --> 00:52.420
will make that list, too.

00:52.440 --> 00:54.509
- What?
- Who are you?

00:54.510 --> 00:56.850
Bro, the Miles I know would
be worried about everything

00:56.860 --> 00:58.699
that could go wrong and
prepare himself for,

00:58.700 --> 00:59.780
like, disappointment.

00:59.800 --> 01:01.320
Okay, well, what can I say?

01:01.350 --> 01:03.239
I am in a positive state of mind.

01:03.240 --> 01:04.440
- Really?
- Yeah.

01:04.450 --> 01:06.199
Even after your disaster
of a date with Cara?

01:06.200 --> 01:08.349
Whoa, whoa, whoa, who said
it was ever a disaster?

01:08.350 --> 01:11.759
Uh, you did, unless I'm
missing something.

01:11.760 --> 01:12.769
Well, you know, my friend,

01:12.770 --> 01:15.859
a gentleman never kisses and tells.

01:15.860 --> 01:17.599
You kissed?

01:17.600 --> 01:19.620
Miles, this is huge!
Miles, that's great!

01:19.630 --> 01:21.940
Okay, yes, yes, we kissed, but we're...

01:21.960 --> 01:24.580
we're taking our time, okay?
Seeing what happens.

01:24.600 --> 01:26.939
Okay, you've been taking your
time for a couple months now.

01:26.940 --> 01:29.509
I suggest speeding things up a little.

01:29.510 --> 01:31.539
You know what? I know,
we should go, like,

01:31.540 --> 01:33.540
on a double date when Jaya comes back.

01:33.550 --> 01:35.879
One step at a time, Rakesh. I gotta go.

01:35.880 --> 01:38.480
I'm meeting the head of FreeVerse here.

01:38.500 --> 01:39.640
All right-y, good luck, man.

01:41.160 --> 01:43.820
I apologize for not getting
back to you sooner.

01:43.850 --> 01:46.300
We get hundreds of podcast
submissions every month,

01:46.310 --> 01:47.599
and I listen to all of them.

01:47.600 --> 01:49.400
Wow, that is dedication.

01:49.440 --> 01:50.740
I think FreeVerse can put

01:50.750 --> 01:52.359
The Millennial Prophet on the map.

01:52.360 --> 01:55.069
Just like Serial did for
This American Life.

01:55.070 --> 01:57.440
Well, that sounds great.

01:57.450 --> 01:59.160
But there's just one thing.

01:59.170 --> 02:01.939
Look, I've been down this road before,

02:01.940 --> 02:04.039
okay, and I know that at a certain point

02:04.040 --> 02:05.879
someone's gonna ask me
to change my message.

02:05.880 --> 02:07.349
I won't.

02:07.350 --> 02:10.400
You've got lightning in a bottle, Miles.

02:10.419 --> 02:13.149
We can't pay you much, and you'd
have to record from home.

02:13.150 --> 02:16.840
But the upside is, no one is
looking over your shoulder.

02:16.850 --> 02:19.459
The only thing we ask for in
return is that we maintain

02:19.460 --> 02:21.659
exclusive rights to our
shows and content.

02:21.660 --> 02:24.359
We wouldn't want anyone else
talking about The God Account.

02:24.360 --> 02:27.180
Other than that, you run your show.

02:27.240 --> 02:30.699
I, um...

02:30.700 --> 02:32.660
I... I don't know what to say.

02:32.680 --> 02:34.320
Say you'll think about it.

02:37.120 --> 02:39.479
"That's Amore." I love that song.

02:39.480 --> 02:41.279
Didn't know it was a make-out song.

02:41.280 --> 02:44.620
Okay, we didn't make out.
What are you, like, 12?

02:44.630 --> 02:46.779
In times like this I
tend to revert back.

02:46.780 --> 02:49.340
- I need details.
- Like, what?

02:49.350 --> 02:50.939
Like, how was the kiss?

02:50.940 --> 02:52.860
Are you going out again?
How was the kiss?

02:52.880 --> 02:55.200
Okay, all right. The kiss was...

02:56.240 --> 02:58.529
Pretty great.

02:58.530 --> 03:00.469
And, yes, we're going out again,

03:00.470 --> 03:04.179
but we both just feel like
this is something special

03:04.180 --> 03:07.419
and we don't see the upside
in rushing into anything.

03:07.420 --> 03:08.769
Okay...

03:08.770 --> 03:11.420
This is a nice office. Quaint.

03:11.540 --> 03:13.479
Mr. Hughes.

03:13.480 --> 03:15.479
- So nice to meet you. I'm...
- Cara Bloom. Yes, I know.

03:15.480 --> 03:17.820
Did you think I walked
in here by mistake?

03:17.850 --> 03:19.620
Well, I thought it was a possibility.

03:19.640 --> 03:21.189
It wasn't.

03:21.190 --> 03:23.169
I've been meaning to swing
by to meet the journalist

03:23.170 --> 03:25.700
who turned down the big job in features.

03:25.760 --> 03:27.880
Not a bad way to catch the boss' eye.

03:28.690 --> 03:30.099
Thank you?

03:30.100 --> 03:33.169
- We should talk.
- Y... yeah, do you wanna...

03:33.170 --> 03:35.080
No, I meant lunch.

03:35.970 --> 03:38.350
- Tomorrow.
- Sure.

03:38.380 --> 03:40.399
Do you mind telling me
what this is about?

03:40.400 --> 03:42.269
Ah, what fun would that be?

03:42.270 --> 03:43.799
My assistant, Lydia, will be in touch

03:43.800 --> 03:45.980
with the details. See you then.

03:47.200 --> 03:49.879
Uh, the editor-in-chief of "Catapult"

03:49.880 --> 03:51.060
just asked you to lunch.

03:51.070 --> 03:53.720
Yeah, question is why?

03:56.880 --> 03:59.199
They have an area for the Civil War

03:59.200 --> 04:00.429
and all the uniforms.

04:00.430 --> 04:03.110
- They have a planetarium.
- What?

04:03.120 --> 04:05.819
And they have a whole
wing just for dinosaurs.

04:05.820 --> 04:07.100
Wow.

04:07.120 --> 04:10.820
The only problem is, the
field trip costs $40.

04:13.300 --> 04:15.240
I... I don't need to go.

04:16.160 --> 04:19.180
Know what? You're gonna go.

04:19.200 --> 04:20.839
It's a lot of money.

04:20.880 --> 04:23.179
Well, it's a good thing that, uh,

04:23.180 --> 04:25.520
I got the job interview tomorrow.

04:28.140 --> 04:31.019
And once you get the job we
can move into our castle

04:31.020 --> 04:32.040
and raise our flag.

04:37.670 --> 04:40.899
Assuming we make it out
of here in one piece.

04:40.900 --> 04:43.440
Did you hear that?

04:43.460 --> 04:46.809
Dragons. Don't worry.

04:48.410 --> 04:50.060
The king must be protected!

04:50.070 --> 04:51.860
I am the dragon slayer!

04:54.880 --> 04:58.040
- Oh, man, that was close.
- Sorry about that.

04:58.050 --> 05:00.360
No, no, they don't
usually come down here.

05:01.190 --> 05:02.520
How do you know?

05:02.530 --> 05:04.120
I, too, am a dragon slayer.

05:04.140 --> 05:05.940
But shh. Don't tell anyone.

05:05.960 --> 05:07.740
I have to keep my identity a secret.

05:10.140 --> 05:12.259
Hey, this is our stop, buddy.

05:12.260 --> 05:14.329
How about you and I go to Metro Diner.

05:14.330 --> 05:15.639
Celebrate my interview.

05:15.640 --> 05:16.650
- Yes!
- Yeah?

05:16.660 --> 05:17.880
- All right.
- And don't worry.

05:17.890 --> 05:19.460
Your secret's safe with me.

05:19.470 --> 05:22.209
I appreciate it.

05:22.210 --> 05:24.339
Oh, hey. Good luck tomorrow.

05:24.340 --> 05:25.609
Thank you!

05:27.460 --> 05:30.220
_

05:40.690 --> 05:43.719
